I consider it totally unnecessary for a street engine, but if I was going 
to do it I would find out how Bergs advises. They are the masters when it 
comes to modifications of T-I engines that actually work well, maintaining 
good reliability and longevity. Go to their site and buy their procedural 
literature and parts and aim for success. 
